<Paragraph>
Tree Navigator is used to navigate up/down the item based on hierarchy. This sample showcases the important capabilities of the tree navigator control.
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>The visual styles denote  built-in themes, including metro, office themes, visual studio, etc.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Supports two types of navigation mode: </Paragraph>
		<Paragraph>
		- In default mode, the parent item can be displayed at the top of tree navigator with back button, and the child elements are placed at below to the parent item.
		</Paragraph>
		<Paragraph>
		- In extended mode, both parent and child item(s) are displayed in stack position.
		</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>
